   nonsynonymous substitutions, or small indels with population size. These
   results contrast with our previous analysis of mitochondrial DNA
   mutations and nuclear copy-number changes in these MA lines, and suggest
   that nuclear base substitutions and small indels are under less
   stringent purifying selection compared to the former mutational classes.
